@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "For schools & coaches";
}

<section class="py-5 bg-light">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted fw-semibold mb-2">
            PARTNERS · TEACHERS · COACHES
        </p>
        <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold mb-3">
            For schools, coaches & community leaders
        </h1>
        <p class="lead text-muted mb-4">
            Some of the most trusted stories on UpliftBridge come through the people who see
            students and families every day – teachers, school staff, coaches and community
            workers. This page explains how we can work together.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="pb-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3">What partnership can look like</h2>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                You help identify students or families with clear, one-time needs:
                                exam fees, uniforms, basic equipment, travel to competitions, or short
                                term support during a difficult season.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                Together we write a simple, respectful story that protects privacy
                                but explains why this gift would make a real difference.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                When possible, funds are channeled through the school or program
                                so that purchases can be verified (for example, receipts for fees or
                                equipment).
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-0">
                                We encourage age-appropriate thank-you notes so donors can see the
                                impact without placing pressure on the student.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                        <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3">What we ask from partners</h2>
                        <ul class="mb-0">
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                A short confirmation (email or letterhead) that the student or family
                                is known to you and that the need is genuine.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                Help setting realistic goals and timelines so no one is disappointed.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-2">
                                A commitment to use gifts only for the purpose described, or to let us
                                know if the situation changes.
                            </li>
                            <li class="mb-0">
                                A spirit of kindness: we never want students to feel shame or pressure
                                because help was requested on their behalf.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-5">
                <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                        <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted fw-semibold mb-2">
                            EXAMPLES
                        </p>
                        <h3 class="h5 fw-bold mb-3">Needs that often fit well</h3>
                        <ul class="mb-3">
                            <li>Entrance exam fees for a promising student.</li>
                            <li>Running shoes or uniforms for a dedicated athlete.</li>
                            <li>Basic laptop or tablet for online learning.</li>
                            <li>Art, music or science supplies that keep a talent alive.</li>
                            <li>Travel costs to an important educational event.</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p class="mb-0 text-muted">
                            If you are unsure whether a need fits, you can always start by sharing
                            the situation privately. We will help you decide if UpliftBridge is the
                            right place, or suggest other options.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card shadow-sm border-0">
                    <div class="card-body p-4">
                        <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted fw-semibold mb-2">
                            HOW TO BEGIN
                        </p>
                        <ol class="mb-3">
                            <li>Choose one student, family or team you would like to support.</li>
                            <li>Gather the basic details: what is needed, how much, and by when.</li>
                            <li>Contact UpliftBridge or submit a draft need through the site.</li>
                            <li>We review, refine and publish the story together.</li>
                        </ol>
                        <p class="mb-0 text-muted">
                            Over time, we hope to build long-term relationships with schools and
                            community groups who share the same quiet joy of giving.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
